{"title":"An Open Letter To The Go Team About Try","description":"“Once a language gets complex enough, programming in it is more like carving out a subset from an infinite sea of features, most of which we’ll never learn. Once a language feels infinite, the costs of adding further features to it are no longer apparent\u0026rdquo;. - Mark Miller The new try proposal is an addition to the language that introduces a second mechanic to handle errors. It is being introduced in response to data gathered from the 2018 Go Survey and a review of proposals that were submitted during the Go 2 proposal process.","thumbnail_url":"","provider_name":"","provider_url":"https://www.ardanlabs.com","author_name":"William KennedyJuly 1, 2019"}